sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant MF as Market Fetcher
    participant MD as Market Data
    participant IE as Indicator Engine
    participant SE as Signal Engine
    participant RE as Risk Engine
    participant NA as Narrative Agent
    participant OE as Order Executor
    participant GC as Gate Client
    participant EX as Exchange

    MF->>EX: Request latest market data
    EX-->>MF: Return price feed (OHLCV, orderbook, depth)
    MF->>MD: Normalize and store market data

    MD->>IE: Provide cleaned market data
    IE-->>IE: Compute indicators (RSI, MA, volatility)
    IE->>SE: Send indicator snapshot

    SE-->>SE: Evaluate strategy conditions
    SE->>RE: Emit potential trade signal

    RE-->>RE: Apply risk rules (exposure, max loss, cooldown)
    RE->>NA: Send validated signal

    NA-->>NA: Generate narrative context and confidence score
    NA->>OE: Approve trade with narrative confidence

    OE->>GC: Build order payload (size, side, type)
    GC->>EX: Submit order to exchange
    EX-->>GC: Return order confirmation

    GC->>OE: Execution result
    OE->>MD: Log trade and update state
